snippet.textDisplay: The bed mismatching the cab has nothing to do with the frame height.  The problem is that the current-generation Super Duty Medium Duty uses the body of the previous-generation Super Duty Pick Up/ Chassis Cab, so the body lines don't match.  If they would've used the steel bed instead of the new aluminum bed, it would match.
snippet.textOriginal: The bed mismatching the cab has nothing to do with the frame height.  The problem is that the current-generation Super Duty Medium Duty uses the body of the previous-generation Super Duty Pick Up/ Chassis Cab, so the body lines don't match.  If they would've used the steel bed instead of the new aluminum bed, it would match.
